              <tbody>
                <tr><td>03/12/2026</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Progress Note</td><td>CC: Fibromyalgia flare, cancer survivorship follow-up.
HPI: 62yo female, 3 years post left lumpectomy + radiation for stage IIA ER+/PR+/HER2- breast cancer. On anastrozole x 3 years (planned 5-year course). Oncology last visit 01/2026 -- NED. Reports fibromyalgia flare this month: widespread pain, fatigue, poor sleep. Fibromyalgia Impact Questionnaire score 58 (moderate-severe). Joint pain may be mixed fibro + aromatase inhibitor arthralgia.
PE: 18-point tender point exam: 14/18 positive. Joints -- no effusion, full ROM. Breast exam: surgical site well-healed, no masses.
Assessment:
# Fibromyalgia (M79.7): Flare. Duloxetine + pregabalin at good doses. Add PT referral for aquatic therapy. Sleep hygiene review.
# Breast cancer survivorship (Z85.3): NED. Anastrozole continue. Mammogram due 06/2026.
# AI arthralgia (M25.50): Contributing to fibro flare. Consider switching to letrozole if intolerable.
# Osteopenia (M85.80): On alendronate + calcium/D. DEXA due 09/2026.
# Insomnia: Zolpidem PRN. Discussed CBT-I as alternative.
Plan: PT referral. Continue meds. Mammogram ordered. DEXA in 6 months. Oncology 6 months. Return 6 weeks for pain reassessment.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </text>
        </section>
